cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of task assignment in spatial crowdsourcing, which involves the use of databases, artificial intelligence, and machine learning techniques to optimize the assignment of tasks to workers. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes approximation algorithms to deal with the NP-hard problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of prediction methods to estimate future worker and task distributions involves statistical inference and machine learning, which are covered under the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.LG.
